# <%= current_page.data.title %>

This document covers a high level patching example for ExternalDNS. Please see [Patching AKS Apps](patching-aks-apps.html)
for a lower level example with more information.

## How We Use ExternalDNS

[ExternalDNS](https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/external-dns) synchronizes exposed Kubernetes Services and Ingresses
with DNS providers, in our case Azure DNS.

We use ExternalDNS in the **dev** and **preview** environments to automatically set up domains for PR-related ad-hoc
environments. When an application team raises a PR, an ephemeral environment is spun up and ExternalDNS creates the DNS
records needed to reach it, then cleans them up when the PR environment is torn down.

It is therefore only installed on the following AKS clusters:

- **SDS dev**: `ss-dev-00-aks`
- **CFT preview**: `cft-preview-00-aks`

The DNS zones used for these ad-hoc environments are:

- [dev.platform.hmcts.net](https://portal.azure.com/#@HMCTS.NET/resource/subscriptions/1baf5470-1c3e-40d3-a6f7-74bfbce4b348/resourceGroups/core-infra-intsvc-rg/providers/Microsoft.Network/privateDnsZones/dev.platform.hmcts.net/resourceOverviewId)
- [preview.platform.hmcts.net](https://portal.azure.com/#@HMCTS.NET/resource/subscriptions/1baf5470-1c3e-40d3-a6f7-74bfbce4b348/resourceGroups/core-infra-intsvc-rg/providers/Microsoft.Network/privateDnsZones/preview.platform.hmcts.net/resourceOverviewId)

## Patching

Review the [ExternalDNS Releases](https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/external-dns/releases) and the
[Helm chart releases](https://artifacthub.io/packages/helm/external-dns/external-dns) pages to check for breaking changes
before updating.

As ExternalDNS is only deployed to dev and preview, you can patch one environment at a time. Patch and test in **dev** first,
then move on to **preview**.

### SDS

Create a PR in sds-flux-config to patch ExternalDNS in SDS: [example PR](https://github.com/hmcts/sds-flux-config/pull/8517).

### CFT

Create a PR in cnp-flux-config to patch ExternalDNS in CFT: [example PR](https://github.com/hmcts/cnp-flux-config/pull/45213).

## Post Patching Checks

ExternalDNS is deployed into the `admin` namespace (the Helm release is named `external-dns` and the deployment is
`external-dns-external-dns-chart`).

First confirm the Helm release has updated to the new version:

```bash
kubectl get hr external-dns -n admin
```

Check the ExternalDNS pods are running and healthy:

```bash
kubectl get pods -n admin -l app.kubernetes.io/name=external-dns-chart
```

Tail the logs to confirm the sync loop is reconciling without errors:

```bash
kubectl logs -n admin deploy/external-dns-external-dns-chart -f
```

You should see the sync loop running on its interval and reporting that records are up to date (or creating/updating
records as needed) with no authentication or permission errors.

Once you are happy that ExternalDNS is working in dev, repeat the patch and the checks for preview.

